status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ft6kl","text":"Add 25 µl B-beads to each lysate in well 1 with a multichannel pipette and cover all other rows while pipetting into one row --\u003e for 96 samples + 2 buffer volumes, fill 2,450 µl B-beads into a reagent matrix","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2v6lu","text":"Add 425 µl MWA2 buffer to each sample with a multichannel pipette (note: protocol says 475 µl buffer MWA2 but wells would overflow), cover all other rows while pipetting into one row --\u003e for 96 samples + 2 buffer volumes, fill 41.65 mL MWA2 buffer into a reagent matrix; mix samples, buffer, and beads in well by pipetting 10x up and down after transferring the buffer to the samples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bkcv2","text":"Hold the magnet into well 1, move it around for 30 secs (to catch all magnetic beads (probably unnecessary but it made me feel better))","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c8tqd","text":"Move the magnet into well 2, DON’T discharge the cover plate (beads will continue to stick to magnets and buffers will interact with beads on the magnet), wait for 3 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"99rto","text":"Move the magnet into well 3, wait for 3 for min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5mv29","text":"Move the magnet into well 4, wait for 3 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a328f","text":"Move the magnet out of well 4, air dry beads for 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjjgb","text":"Move the magnet into well 5, wait for 10 min (nucleic acids unbind from magnetic beads and go into final elution)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9hqn3","text":"Cover the plate containing the eluates with foil and store it in a -80 freezer (-20 is sufficient for DNA samples)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"sjo5","text":"Move the magnet out of well 3, air dry beads for 5 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"40d6u","text":"Move the magnet to well 6, wait for 25 min (nucleic acids unbind from magnetic beads and go into solution, DNA is digested) (note: the protocol says to wait for 15 min but I still had DNA in my samples after 15 min)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"69jvr","text":"Take the magnet including the magnetic beads out and set them aside on the drying rack","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2fsqb","text":"Add 350 µl buffer MWA2 to well 6, cover all other rows while pipetting into one row, mix by pipetting 10x up and down, wait for 5 min (preparing nucleic acids to rebind) (350 µl x 96 = 33.6 mL, use the same technique for this step as when prepping the wells: fill up the reagent matrix to 25 mL, use up the mix, then refill to same reagent matrix to 1/3rd)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c2bf5","text":"Move the magnet including the magnetic beads back in well 6, wait for 5 min (nucleic acids re-bind to beads)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
